{
  "stem": "3605.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Even before the war, he used to go there with my brother for the High Holidays.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he used to say-- talk with the rabbi how what can help and what we can do, and what we should do.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the rabbi-- he was a very wonderful, realistic, smart man.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He says, Joseph, I cannot help myself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How can I help you?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We just have to trust-- maybe tomorrow the Mashiach will come.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the Jews never gave up the hope.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Mashiach was--?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Mashiach was the-- the-- the prophet-- the Messiah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Jews believe in the coming of the Messiah, when the lion is going to be able to live with the lamb, and when there is not going to be a war, when the humanity is going to reign all over.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and that was the hope.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But, instead of it, early in the morning, after Yom Kippur, the Day of Atonement, the ghetto was surrounded.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I got caught there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father-- there was a deportation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father had a permit that I bought him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we were going through the selection, he was told to stay, and I-- since I had illegal papers-- I was still illegal, to begin with-- I wasn't going to show them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Right away, they directed me to go to the transports out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they had rows of five [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] cattle wagons waiting there for the people on the Umschlagplatz, which was the-- the place of segregation of Jews for the deportation.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember staying in a row, pretty close to the wagons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then I ran away to another row, a little farther away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were my aunts and uncles.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I could see my cousins.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
